@page "/workouts/arms"

<h3>Arm Workouts</h3>

<div class="workout-container">
    <h4>Barbell Curls</h4>
    <p>Description: Barbell curls primarily target the biceps muscles.</p>
</div>

<div class="workout-container">
    <h4>Hammer Curls</h4>
    <p>Description: Hammer curls target the brachialis and brachioradialis muscles in addition to the biceps.</p>
</div>

<div class="workout-container">
    <h4>Dumbbell Curls</h4>
    <p>Description: Dumbbell curls isolate the biceps and also engage the forearms and grip muscles.</p>
</div>

<div class="workout-container">
    <h4>Tricep Dips</h4>
    <p>Description: Tricep dips target the triceps muscles and also engage the chest and shoulders.</p>
</div>

<div class="workout-container">
    <h4>Tricep Extensions</h4>
    <p>Description: Tricep extensions, whether with dumbbells or cables, effectively isolate the triceps muscles.</p>
</div>

<div class="workout-container">
    <h4>Preacher Curls</h4>
    <p>Description: Preacher curls target the biceps and help isolate the muscle for better development.</p>
</div>

<div class="workout-container">
    <h4>Concentration Curls</h4>
    <p>Description: Concentration curls emphasize the biceps brachii muscle and improve arm strength and definition.</p>
</div>

